I think ill defenatly use it to open a single pull soloing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umadleon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Madleon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/16/01 8:33:13 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.packetlost.com/ho/im/headache.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What you think about our OTHER SoL spells</span><hr size=1> I'm with Grimstaff on this one. They put little effort into this and aren't improving on the class very much in my opinion. <br>
<br>
1. Familiars. <br>
Ok, while it will be a novelty overall I don't see this as much of an improvement. Not everyone is level 60 and will this even stack with our other buffs such as Shield of the Magi? I'd like higher resists as much as the next person but if these don't stack nor if the 3 mana tick won't stack with epic, I'll be very dissapointed. What they should of done is just give us a drake form with these same properties including a non reagent based levitate, at least that'd be a step in the right direction.<br>
<br>
2. New O'Kiell's. <br>
Errm, why even bother...we already have 2 of these no one uses! I have them on my boots and the only time they EVER get used is when we're fighting a high end mob where we need FR. And even then, the duration is so short, what's the point...this one can rot wherever they sell it. <br>
<br>
3. Translocate Safe Spot<br>
Uhh..this is just another obvious point that Verant has nothing left to be original. Really, I'd like to stick up for them but when they add crap like this and expect us to pay MORE money for it, well they won't get my money. Although this is a raid friendly spell this is why I have Evacuate already. the TL's are a nice addition as it makes us able to be more lazy but this shouldn't be viewed as a &quot;major upgrade for wizards!!!&quot; <br>
<br>
4. Eye of Al'Kabor<br>
Al been pimpin Luclin so far, would it surprise you? I've always been a fan of the Eye of Zomm and although I'd love to see an upgraded version, it has such limited uses I still don't consider this an upgrade worthy of me having to BUY IT. Aside from all the upgrades to it, my main problem with the Eye of Zomm is, it doesn't work very well. So will this one actually work? Riiiight.<br>
<br>
5. Ice DD + Root<br>
While this does have potential again, I don't see it as something that revolutionizes our class like some additions to other classes for Luclin. This is really our only upgrade as it's the only spell used in battle. Seems weird since we're supposed to be the damage kings. I was kind of hoping for a Disease or Poison nuke <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Anyways, I doubt it checks on Ice for the root portion. I will bet all my plat it's a magic based root that does Ice based damage. So...if the mob resists the root will he resist the dd? And vice versa? I'll stick with good old level 4 root thank you very much.<br>
<br>
And Verant. If you expect consumers to buy your new expansion pack, howabout next time take your time, develop a good gameplan and quit looking over your shoulder at these other MMORPG's coming to knock u off the top. No one lives forever <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
